[{"id":"FT546050","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"The figure shows 4 parallel, horizontal arrows pointing to the right that are labeled vector B.  There is a point labeled vector v between the second arrow and the third arrow.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/4867dbac7dfbfb4b36b93347832da6a2/original.png\" width=\"200\" /></p>\n\n<p>An electron travels through a uniform magnetic field&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"right arrow set over cap b\"><math> <mrow> <mover> <mi>B</mi> <mo>→</mo> </mover> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;directed to the right. The electron’s velocity&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"right arrow set over v\"><math> <mrow> <mover> <mi>v</mi> <mo>→</mo> </mover> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;is directed out of the page, as shown in the figure above. The direction of the force on the electron due to the magnetic field at the instant shown is</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<p>toward the top of the page</p>","<p>toward the bottom of the page</p>","<p>to the left</p>","<p>to the right</p>","<p>into the page</p>"],"answer":0}]